The equivalent circuit model of S-TENG which hybrids TE and SE is shown in Fig. 3c. As these two effects share the same electrodes, they are connected in parallel. In TE case, the TENG can be viewed as a capacitor (CT) using the capacitor model14. The equivalent circuit of SE is an open-circuit voltage source connected with a resistance (Rs). The whole circuit also satisfies Thevenin’s Theorem, whose output voltage (VAB) is:2VAB=−QCT+VTE=VSE−IRs\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
